<?xml version="1.0"?>
<gpx xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1" xmlns:gpxx="http://www.garmin.com/xmlschemas/GpxExtensions/v3" creator="CALTOPO" version="1.1"><metadata><name><![CDATA[Soda Springs Loop]]></name></metadata><trk><name>Soda Springs Loop</name><desc>Popularity: 1/5
Difficulty: 3/5
Dates: 10/1 - 6/1
Parking: Diablo Canyon Recreation Area trailhead. It's got a bathroom and lots of parking. Can be crowded with rock climbers, but I've never seen the lot full.

I love this loop. You get to see a bit of everything: Diablo Canyon, the Rio Grande, White Rock Canyon. A fairly flat run except for the steep climb up onto the Caja del Rio plateau and the steep descent back down into Diablo Canyon. If you plan to go to Diablo Canyon and have a time and energy I would suggest doing this loop rather than "just" Diablo Canyon to the Rio Grande and back. 

Footing in the arroyo to the Rio Grande can be very loose sand if it hasn't rained or snowed recently. Pay close attention so you don't get lost or miss a turn, the turns aren't in-your-face obvious or well signed.</desc><trkseg><trkpt lat="35.80459179681884" lon="-106.1362414126587"><ele>1782.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80458000000001" lon="-106.13626"><ele>1782.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80452" lon="-106.13665000000003"><ele>1779.0596264003625</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80467" lon="-106.13713000000001"><ele>1779.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80479" lon="-106.13734999999997"><ele>1778.0425854621656</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80528" lon="-106.13855000000001"><ele>1775.666136080348</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80525" lon="-106.13873999999998"><ele>1774.8578467222949</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80505" lon="-106.13887"><ele>1773.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80542" lon="-106.14083"><ele>1769.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80567" lon="-106.14138000000003"><ele>1767.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80632" lon="-106.14204000000001"><ele>1769.75143029592</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80652" lon="-106.14267999999998"><ele>1766.130683619629</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.8066" lon="-106.14300000000003"><ele>1760.016856318815</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80687" lon="-106.14315999999997"><ele>1780.607359266768</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80689" lon="-106.14337999999998"><ele>1766.2311312137765</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80675" lon="-106.14386999999999"><ele>1758.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80655" lon="-106.14429999999999"><ele>1755.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80672" lon="-106.14453000000003"><ele>1758.9934253804386</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80669" lon="-106.14495"><ele>1767.5389855764806</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80648" lon="-106.14504"><ele>1752.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80644" lon="-106.14508999999998"><ele>1752.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80636" lon="-106.14537000000001"><ele>1751.2212938731932</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80626" lon="-106.14557000000002"><ele>175